00:09:14.960 --> 00:09:18.880
present only on the male-specific part of the Y chromosome, we

163
00:09:18.920 --> 00:09:22.840
can say which cells are Loy cells and not, here shown in red.

164
00:09:25.020 --> 00:09:28.860
And so far, as I mentioned, all studied men and tissues that has

165
00:09:28.920 --> 00:09:31.140
been studied, you find these Loy cells.

166
00:09:31.360 --> 00:09:34.270
So it's extremely prevalent. And

167
00:09:35.200 --> 00:09:37.340
not only that, that we all have it,

168
00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:40.720
it also occurs multiple times

169
00:09:41.600 --> 00:09:43.560
