213
00:12:04.400 --> 00:12:08.020
So as Don mentioned in his talk, it's been known

214
00:12:08.240 --> 00:12:12.100
since this paper in '63 that loss of Y is a very frequent event in the

215
00:12:12.140 --> 00:12:15.936
hematopoietic system of aging men.But it was long thought that it was

216
00:12:16.176 --> 00:12:17.176
phenotypically neutral.

217
00:12:18.096 --> 00:12:18.616
But this was

218
00:12:20.836 --> 00:12:23.456
overruled by this paper that we had.

219
00:12:23.576 --> 00:12:25.236
So we basically found this

