222
00:12:31.716 --> 00:12:34.216
Quite small cohort, but had some benefits.

223
00:12:34.256 --> 00:12:37.936
The individuals was kind of old, and we had very long follow-up

224
00:12:37.976 --> 00:12:38.296
times.

225
00:12:39.276 --> 00:12:42.736
So here we identified that men with loss of Y in more than one-third of their blood

