233
00:13:07.316 --> 00:13:10.456
So this is all loss of Y in blood and increased risk for cancers.

234
00:13:10.956 --> 00:13:12.256
So as you can see, it's both

235
00:13:13.656 --> 00:13:15.536
male specific cancers and

236
00:13:16.456 --> 00:13:17.896
non-sex specific cancers,

237
00:13:19.296 --> 00:13:21.176
and also hematological malignancies.

238
00:13:22.096 --> 00:13:23.956
So in this part of the presentation,

239
00:13:25.076 --> 00:13:28.796
I think it's good to mention that I will not talk about what

